        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 3:51PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 351 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Detroit, or 10 miles west of Hamilton, moving east at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Detroit, Henson Springs, Pearces Mill, Rankin Fite Airport, Brinn,
Twin, Hackleburg, Brilliant, Weston, Byrd, Hamilton, Bexar, Marion
County Public Lake, Pikeville, and Guin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
northwestern and west central Alabama.</instruction>
